external_knowledge:
- The term 'sentiment' here refers to the emotional tone or attitude conveyed by the text of the transcript;
- 'Researchers' notes' imply annotations made by users classified as researchers, typically indicating their interest or observations about specific parts of the transcripts;
- 'Top three' implies a ranking based on the average sentiment scores, with higher scores indicating more positive sentiments.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
   FROM annotated_transcripts 
   WHERE is_public = 1;

SELECT annotation, annotation_type
FROM annotated_transcripts
WHERE is_public = 1;

SELECT COUNT(transcript_id) AS total_transcripts, MAX(length) AS longest_transcript_length
FROM transcripts
WHERE year = 2023;

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_sentiment
FROM analysis
WHERE metric = 'sentiment';

SELECT text
FROM transcripts
WHERE transcript_id = 1;
